longBusinessSummary: Saga Communications, Inc., a broadcast company, acquires, develops, and operates broadcast properties in the United States. The company's radio stations employ various programming formats, including classic hits, adult hits, top 40, country, country legends, mainstream/hot/soft adult contemporary, pure oldies, classic rock, and news/talk. It owned FM and AM radio stations, and metro signals serving various markets. The company was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Grosse Pointe Farms, Michigan.
